**not meant for a revival, just learn from this or use this to test**
1. download a rcc (archive.roblonium.com has 2015+ archive.org has 2007-2008)
2. use cmd/bat to navigate and start the rcc app with `-console`
3. once started, download soapui (can be found in <#1247332138995552307>)
4. open soap ui, localhost/127.0.0.1, roblox.com, and the right port should already be set
5. select openjobex for the command type and in the script box paste in a script based on your rcc:

2007/8:
```lua
game.Players:CreateLocalPlayer(0)
game.Players.Player:LoadCharacter()
print(game:GetService("ThumbnailGenerator"):Click("PNG", 500, 500, true))
```

2015+:
```lua
game:GetService("ContentProvider"):SetBaseUrl("http://www.roblox.com")
game:GetService("ScriptContext").ScriptsDisabled = true
game.Players:CreateLocalPlayer(0)
game.Players.Player1:LoadCharacter()
print(game:GetService("ThumbnailGenerator"):Click("PNG", 500, 500, true))
```

if u want to load a place just do `game:Load("rbxasset://place.rbxl")`. the rbxl file should be located in your rcc's content folder in this example, but you can use urls aswell, only http:// works i believe, not https://

your rcc window should spit out a long base64 hash, copy that and paste it onto a base64 decoder site and decode it to an image, there you have your render

obviously revivals automate all these actions in the backend but it's up to you how you do that
if you want to add accessories/body colors to ur character just download the accessory/body color object as xml files and then set Player.CharacterAppearance to be the path to each file seperated by semi colons (;)
